--- title: "Manuscript Files" format: html: code-fold: true code-summary: "Show the code" --- > This page shows all graphs and tables used in the manuscript along with the code used. Additional univariate frequencies of covariates not shown in the manuscript are shown in the demographics table. # Frequency Statistics ## Table 1: Demographic Information: ::: {.cell} ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} demographics_cc <- bns_combined %>% select(age, gender, race_eth, monthly_hh_income, academic_level, Cohort, school2, calfresh3, calfresh_eligible, cooking_confident, health_conscious, physical_activity, ssb_cat, ff_cat, fruits3, food_insecure_2item, units, paid_work_hours) cc <- demographics_cc %>% tbl_summary(statistic = list( all_continuous() ~ "Mean: {mean}, Median: {median}, SD: {sd}", all_categorical() ~ "{n} ({p}%)"), missing_text= "Missing (n)") demographics_imp <- bns_combined_imputed_df %>% select(age, gender, race_eth, monthly_hh_income, academic_level, Cohort, school2, calfresh3, calfresh_eligible, cooking_confident, health_conscious, physical_activity, ssb_cat, ff_cat, fruits3, food_insecure_2item, units, paid_work_hours) imp <- demographics_imp %>% tbl_summary(statistic = list( all_continuous() ~ "Mean: {mean}, Median: {median}, SD: {sd}", all_categorical() ~ "{n} ({p}%)"), missing_text= "Missing (n)") tbl_merge(tbls = list(cc, imp), tab_spanner = c("**Complete Case Demographics**", "**Imputed Demographics**")) %>% as_kable_extra( booktabs = TRUE, longtable = TRUE, linesep = "" ) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

````` ::: ::: ## Figure 2: Fast Food Vs CalFresh ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} bns_combined_imputed_df$ff_cat2 <- recode(bns_combined_imputed_df$ff_cat, "Zer" = "Zero", "1-2 times per week" = "1-2 times", "3-4 times per week" = "3-4 times", "5 or more times per week" = "5 or more times") p2 <- bns_combined_imputed_df %>% select(ff_cat2, calfresh3) %>% na.omit() %>% ggplot(aes(x= ff_cat2, group=calfresh3)) + geom_bar(aes(y = ..prop.., fill = factor(calfresh3)), stat="count", #alpha = c(0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1), colour="black", size=0.6) + geom_text(aes(label = scales::percent(round(..prop.., digits = 2)), y=..prop..), stat= "count", vjust = -.5, size = 6) + labs(y = "Percent of Students") + facet_wrap(~calfresh3, ncol = 1, scales = "free_x") + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent, expand = expansion(mult = c(0.0, 0.85))) + scale_fill_manual(values = chc.palette) + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position="none") + xlab("\nFrequency of Fast-Food Meals Per Week") + theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size = 15), text = element_text(size = 15)) # ggsave("FF_Plot.png", plot = p2, width = 10, height = 8) p2 ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Manuscript-Files_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: ## Figure 3: SSB Vs CalFresh ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} p3 <- bns_combined %>% select(ssb_cat, calfresh3) %>% na.omit() %>% ggplot(aes(x= ssb_cat, group=calfresh3)) + geom_bar(aes(y = ..prop.., fill = factor(calfresh3)), stat="count", #alpha = c(0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1), colour="black", size=0.6) + geom_text(aes(label = scales::percent(round(..prop.., digits = 2)), y=..prop..), stat= "count", vjust = -.5, size = 6) + labs(y = "Percent of Students") + facet_wrap(~calfresh3, ncol = 1, scales = "free_x") + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent, expand = expansion(mult = c(0.0, 1.6))) + scale_fill_manual(values = chc.palette) + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position="none") + xlab("\nOunces of Sugar Sweetened Beverages Consumed Per Day") + theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size = 15), text = element_text(size = 15)) # ggsave("SSB_Plot.png", plot = p3, width = 10, height = 8) p3 ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Manuscript-Files_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: ## Figure 4: F&V Vs CalFresh ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} p1 <- bns_combined_imputed_df %>% select(fruits3, calfresh3) %>% na.omit() %>% ggplot(aes(x= fruits3, group=calfresh3)) + geom_bar(aes(y = ..prop.., fill = factor(calfresh3)), stat="count", #alpha = c(0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1, 0.3, 0.7, 1), colour="black", size=0.6) + geom_text(aes(label = scales::percent(round(..prop.., digits = 2)), y=..prop..), stat= "count", vjust = -.5, size = 6) + labs(y = "Percent of Students") + facet_wrap(~calfresh3, ncol = 1, scales = "free_x") + scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent, expand = expansion(mult = c(0.0, 0.4))) + scale_fill_manual(values = chc.palette) + theme_bw() + theme(legend.position="none") + xlab("\nServings of Fruits and Vegetables Per Day") + theme(strip.text.x = element_text(size = 15), text = element_text(size = 15)) # ggsave("FV_Plot.png", plot = p1, width = 10, height = 8) p1 ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Manuscript-Files_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: # Ordinal Regression Models ##
